    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "Just to clarify, it doesn't cause a \"crash\" - the exceptions I was able to trigger were all caught before they caused any serious problems to the application server itself. The furthest I've seen the exception go up is the worker thread, which I can get to [complain](https://github.com/grpc/grpc/blob/master/src/ruby/lib/grpc/generic/rpc_server.rb#L140), but that doesn't actually break the worker thread. That said, I have no idea if there's required cleanup that is not being performed because it is throwing."
